What\'92s causing this trend of a more positive net flux into the land since the 1980s? In the carbon cycle models it is due to primarily two effects. One is global warming\'92s lengthening of the growing season outside the tropics, allowing plants, especially in the coldest regions, to grow more and store more carbon. The other larger effect is a \\(\\text\{CO\}_2\\) fertilization effect, which stimulates plants to grow faster or larger in a higher-\'ad\\(\\text\{CO\}_2\\) atmosphere. Leaf photosynthesis takes place behind a waxy seal, with gas ports called stomata that can be actively opened and closed. The penalty for opening the stomata is the loss of water as vapor. If the \\(\\text\{CO\}_2\\) concentration in the air is higher, the plants can grow without losing as much water. The enzyme responsible for \\(\\text\{CO\}_2\\) uptake, called rubisco, also runs more quickly at higher \\(\\text\{CO\}_2\\) concentrations. \
